mAI Coach - Requirements 

1) Problem Statement & Scope (Team)  

Primary user: a gym-goer who wants real-time, actionable form feedback on compound lifts such as bench press while lifting alone. 

Secondary user: a coach or friend who reviews set summaries and flags for teaching or feedback. 

Context of use: the iPhone camera records a set; the app overlays a live skeleton, detects form issues (elbow flare/tuck, grip width, bar path), speaks feedback quickly after each rep, and counts reps. 

System boundaries: 

• In scope (v1): on-device pose tracking; steady overlay; rep counting; elbow/hand/bar-path checks; voice feedback; local storage. 

• Out of scope (v1): medical advice; cloud video storage by default; Android build. 

Measurable success criteria (initial): 

• Voice feedback median < 1.0 s from rep end; 95th percentile ≤ 1.5 s. 

• Elbow/hand/bar-path detectors achieve ≥95% sensitivity with ≤2.5% false-positive rate on held-out test clips. 

• Overlay jitter is capped by a numeric threshold; no obvious snaps/teleports during steady phases. 

• App remains crash-free during sets; crash-free rate target ≥99.5% in testing. 

• App can recover from crash (reboot time < 3s).  

Non-goal: this is not medical diagnosis or injury treatment. This is not professional lifting advice by a licensed trainer.  

 

